	<li class="comment even depth-4" id="comment-6261" >
		<div class="c-grav"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/cc6cc5e2318fc6b1d5d7abb0a20e3c6c?s=40&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D40&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-40 photo' height='40' width='40' /></div>
		<div class="c-body">
			<div class="c-head">
				Jozef <span class="c-permalink"><a href="http://www.michaelnielsen.org/ddi/how-the-bitcoin-protocol-actually-works/#comment-6261">permalink</a></span>
			</div>
						<p>You only own that much of bitcoins as others agree you own. So, hardcoded here means it is the original protocol suggested (and supposed) to be honored by all the users. There&#8217;s no use for miner to continue giving himself 25 BTC when it&#8217;s already time for lowering the reward to 12.5, because this reward would not be considered valid by others who respect the original protocol.</p>
						<div class="reply">
							</div>
					</div><!--end c-body-->
