	<ul class="children">
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-admin bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-6304" >
		<div class="c-grav"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/e5cbb32cf54a237e409a3608fc2f88d1?s=40&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D40&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-40 photo' height='40' width='40' /></div>
		<div class="c-body">
			<div class="c-head">
				Michael Nielsen <span class="c-permalink"><a href="http://www.michaelnielsen.org/ddi/how-the-bitcoin-protocol-actually-works/#comment-6304">permalink</a></span>
			</div>
						<p>No, the average number of trials is 16^10.  </p>
<p>(If we repeatedly sample from a Bernoulli random variable with probability p of a success, then the expected number of trials to success is \sum_{n=1}^\infty n p (1-p)^{n-1}, which is easily shown to be 1/p.  The probability p in the proof-of-work is 16^{-10}, so the expected number of trials to success is 16^{10}.)</p>
<p>What important things are missing from the explanation?</p>
